Africa
------
[1] Liberia (Gbarpolu)
Date: Mon 4 May 2015
Source: StarAfrica, APA (African Press Agency) report [edited]
http://en.starafrica.com/news/measles-outbreak-kills-11-children-in-northern-liberia-sources.html


Measles outbreak kills 11 children in northern Liberia
------------------------------------------------------
Measles has claimed the lives of 11 children in Henry Town in north-western Gbarpolu County in northern Liberia. The Liberia News Agency correspondent in the county quotes health officials as saying that the disease claimed the lives of the 11 children within one week.

Meanwhile, the Ministry of health and the Liberia National Red Cross Society in the county over the weekend commenced a training workshop on measles for 50 volunteers and health workers assigned in the town. The Liberia National Red Cross Society - Gbarpolu Chapter and the County Health Team have also begun a 14-day intensive de-worming awareness campaign in the 5 health districts of the county.

Addressing participants at the start of the workshop, LNRCS Field Officer, Seth Tarweh, pointed out that the campaign is aimed at enhancing the government's information dissemination about the measles vaccination campaign that is to be officially launched in Bopolu on 8 May 2015.

