******
[2] Sudan
Date: Thu 30 Apr 2015
Source: AllAfrica, Radio Dabanga (Hilversum) report [summ., edited]
http://allafrica.com/stories/201505040395.html


Sudan: 169 Measles Cases, 27 Deaths Reported in Sudan
-----------------------------------------------------
According to the Ministry of Health, the World Health Organisation (WHO), and UNICEF measles has been reported in 32 localities in 14 states across Sudan. In response, a nationwide measles vaccination campaign was launched on 22 Apr 2015 and will continue for 10 days. Some 1.7 million people aged between 6 months to 15 years in the 28 worst affected localities are targeted. These localities are in Red Sea, Kassala, Sennar, West Darfur, East Darfur, and North Darfur states, OCHA [UN Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs] reported. WHO and UNICEF are supporting the vaccination campaign with logistics, supervision and monitoring, in collaboration with Sudanese non-governmental organisations.

Of the total number of reported measles cases, 69 percent are below 15 years of age, including 52 percent under the age of 5. West Darfur remains the worst affected state, with 441 confirmed cases and 5 deaths. Kassala has had 365 confirmed cases and 5 deaths, while in Red Sea state there have been 263 cases and 4 deaths, UNICEF reported on 23 Apr 2015. Sudan has one of the highest levels of malnutrition in Africa. 36 percent of the children are stunted, which is a primary manifestation of undernutrition. For malnourished children, measles can cause serious complications, including blindness, ear infections, pneumonia, and severe diarrhoea.

