[5] USA (Georgia)
Date: Thu 7 May 2005
Source: 11 Alive, WXIA [edited]
http://www.11alive.com/story/news/local/suwanee/2015/05/06/measles-forsyth-county/70890294/


Student tests positive for measles in Forsyth County, Georgia
-------------------------------------------------------------
An elementary school student in Forsyth County recently tested positive for measles. Amy Bartlett, principal of Sharon Elementary School, sent parents a letter confirming a 3rd grader has the highly infectious disease. "We do not mean to cause alarm but want to keep all of our parents informed when a case has been reported," Bartlett said in the letter.

A fever is usually the 1st sign of a measles infection, followed by a hacking cough, runny nose, and pinkeye. A red or reddish-brown rash the forehead and spreads down over the face, neck and body, then to the arms and feet. Children who develop any measles symptoms should see a healthcare provider as soon as possible.

